cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on distributed graph processing platforms and proposes partitioning strategies for load balancing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the impact of partitioning strategies on Breadth First Search and PageRank algorithms, which are fundamental graph algorithms. 
3. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper deals with analyzing large graphs, which is a common problem in graph databases. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed partitioning strategies on powerlaw and spatio-planar graphs, which are commonly used in social and information networks. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of communication on the performance of distributed graph processing platforms, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture.
